    <stitle>Meritor/WABCO Hydraulic ABS for Medium-Duty Trucks, Buses and Motor Home Chassis - TROUBLESHOOTING AND
        TESTING - GENERAL MAINTENANCE INFORMATION
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="pm" graphiccount="4">
        <title>GENERAL MAINTENANCE INFORMATION</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>There is no regularly scheduled maintenance required for Meritor WABCO D Version Hydraulic ABS.
                However, ABS does not change current vehicle maintenance requirements. For example, it is important that
                the vehicle brake fluid level be properly maintained.
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>System Wiring Information</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Refer to the
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f1004691a">Figure</hotlnk>
                        below for ECU pin identification.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f1004691a" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figR10/R104691A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"/>
                <caption>Figure 13. ECU Pin Identification</caption>
            </figure>
            <para>Wiring may vary, according to the vehicle. Refer to the vehicle specifications for specific wiring
                diagrams. A typical Meritor WABCO 4S/4M Hydraulic ABS wiring diagram appears in the
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1004692b">Figure</hotlnk>
                below.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1004692b" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figR10/R104692B.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"/>
                <caption>Figure 14. Typical Meritor WABCO 4S/4M Hydraulic ABS Wiring Diagram</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f1004693a" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figR10/R104693A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"/>
                <caption>Figure 15. Pin Numbers and Locations (Frame-Mounted ECU)</caption>
            </figure>
            <para>Refer to the
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1004694b">Figure</hotlnk>
                below for the 4S/4M D Version Hydraulic ABS Wiring Diagram
            </para>
            <figure id="f1004694b" figsize="pg-wide">
